description.narrative:
The overall objective of the intervention FCG 2019-2023 (Gender Common Fund and its Strategic Plan 2019-2023) is to contribute to the implementation of relevant and effective actions to reduce gender inequalities at the national level by CSOs, and Government authorities in order to prevent and combat gender-based violence, to promote economic empowerment, to enable greater participation of women in politics and decision-making, and women's and young peoples' involvement in security issues.
The FCG 2019-2023  is based on five strategic axes: Axis 1: Strengthening actions to promote the abandonment of gender based violence (GBV) Axis 2: Economic and political empowerment of women and young people Axis 3: Strengthening gender mainstreaming in the development and monitoring of public policies, projects and programs by institutions and CSOs Axis 4: Involvement of women and youth in the management of security issues  Axis 5: Coordination, monitoring, evaluation, capitalization of achievements and promotion of innovative approaches
The five main expected results are:
- Actions to prevent, reduce and end GBV are strengthened;
- The economic and political empowerment of women and youth are strengthened;
- Gender mainstreaming in the development and monitoring of public policies, projects and programs by institutions and CSOs is strengthened;
- Better involvement of women and youth in the management of security issues is ensured;
- Coordination, monitoring, evaluation, capitalization of achievements and promotion of innovative approaches is ensured.
At the end, women poverty is reduced.
